Meet <b>Lili</b>_Liao, our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>Lili has been camped out at her <a href='/home/?user=lili_liao'>2516-H Broadway Boulevard</a> residence in Lakeview since September 28th, 2007. In a little over two months, Lili has managed to collect nearly twenty trophies. <br><br>Not only does she have trophies for the likes of Sink Three, Home Run Derby, and Tricky Touchdown, but she also has distinguished honors for such socially minded events as Millsberry Match and the Peabody Park Clean Up.<br><br>If you are admiring her trophies, you'll want to look with your eyes and not with your hands, because there's a golden serpent guarding this precious collection. However, you will want to get some hands on experience in Lili's garden.<br><br>She has some nice Tulips and Daisies in bloom right now, and who knows what else is going to sprout up in the next few days. While Lili works in the garden, she's most likely humming a melody from her favorite Jazz, Classic Rock, or Big Band CD. <br><br>With her liking for Jazz, it seems as though Lili has a knack for improvisation. How else do you end up with a spiral staircase and a refrigerator in your walk-in closet? It actually doesn't appear that out of the ordinary. They probably come in handy during a fashion crisis. <br><br>If you should happen to run into Lili, shake her hand and thank her for being such a great citizen.<br></div>
